
[1]immoral

   IMMOR'AL, a. [in and moral.] Inconsistent with moral rectitude;
   contrary to the moral or divine law; wicked; unjust; dishonest;
   vicious. Every action is immoral which contravenes any divine
   precept,or which is contrary to the duties which men owe to each other.

   1. Wicked or unjust in practice; vicious; dishonest; as an immoral man.
   Every man who violates a divine law or a social duty, is immoral but we
   particularly apply the term to a person who habitually violates the
   laws.
